<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="714" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d714">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/8458½: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chilean Minister for Foreign Affairs</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cruchaga</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-04">June 4, 1936</date>.<lb/>[Received June 4—8:20
                                p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Truly regret scope and purpose attached to our memorandum. At no time
                            have we doubted lofty intentions your Government and the very wording of
                            memorandum shows our complete confidence in attitude United States. My
                            desire has been to cooperate with you in warding off such disturbing
                            requests by warning the governments which may wish to formulate or share
                            in one of them that we are unalterably opposed thereto.</p>
                        <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Miguel Cruchaga</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>